<|startoftext|>Worst experience ever. I went in to have the paint wash off of my carpet. When I looked at the photos on yelp the paint looked like it was stuck in an old car. I asked them to do a full dry and clean out the area where the carpet was. They said I would be billed $900 if I didn't. They gave me a $1,800+ tip to get my carpet to be painted right, but since I already had to pay for it, they said I had to pay for it. That was my first and last time being with them.<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>I really like the service. The woman working the register is very friendly and kind. They don't charge a lot for the service so I always go in with an eye to service. Their cakes are good and the desserts are good. My wife gets a gel manicure and I get a pedicure.  I love the gel nails and they are too.  I try to stop there when I'm in the mood for gel manicures and I'm not too happy with the manicures.  The staff is friendly and pleasant and the prices are a bit higher than other nail salons around the area.  I'm definitely coming back.<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>The staff was very nice and helpful. They were very concerned about my husband and I but didn't say anything I was rather upset about. The man at the counter just apologized to the lady and said how hard it was to clean up after I cleaned it. We were told a little over an hour to clean up before my eyes. My hair was very uneven and the trim just wasn't quite as good as I would like the color. I'm definitely going to turn away this business anytime i want to visit this salon<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>The most amazing staff.  Great atmosphere and the people are great too.  Definitely will come back.  They are really hard to see (there are so many people in the area to see and to talk to). The food was amazing too.  The only reason this place is 5 stars is because the food took a while to come out.<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>I had never been to Battista's before but decided to try it since I had heard great reviews.\n\nThis place is definitely worth checking out if you're in the area: you'll be back in an hour or two.  The bar area is great; the food is excellent, and the people are cool.  I was a first-timer on Saturday night and I'm looking forward to every bite on Sunday.  I had a great time in my experience at Battista's.  The food is wonderful and I would definitely order again.  However, the service is HORRIBLE.  The place is not very organized in the kitchen, and they don't always have everything in stock.  They have all kinds of things, most of which I find odd.  I had a great experience at the bar and did not take the photos or even show them, but I did take them.  My husband had the burrito and said it was terrible and he still had the burrito but I was out.  \n\nIf you are looking for great service, go for what you need but be quick and ready to pay for what you get...<|endoftext|>
